        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 1:14AM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 113 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kasson, or near Evansville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Evansville, Henderson, Newburgh, Chandler, Melody Hill, and Kasson.

This includes Interstate 69 in Indiana between Mile Markers 1 and 13.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
